[1] Diarrhea, fatal - Pakistan (Federally Administered Tribal Areas)
Date: Mon 19 Sep 2011
Source: Pakistan Observer [edited]
http://pakobserver.net/detailnews.asp?id=115047


At least 7 people including women and children died and dozens others
were hospitalized after diarrhea broke out in Tirah Valley of Khyber
Agency. According to local sources, due to contaminated water and
unhygienic conditions, epidemics like diarrhea broke out in far flung
and militancy-hit Tirah Valley.

Due to the outbreak of the epidemic and absence of appropriate medical
treatment, 7 people including women and children have died during the
past 2 days. Meanwhile, dozens of other diarrhea patients were shifted
to different hospitals. Most of the hospitals in the troubled area
were closed due to militants' activities and security forces' action,
and there was no staff in the hospitals and Basic Health Units (BHU).

Local sources said that several affected people were in critical
condition as there was no facility of medical treatment in the area.
The dwellers of Tirah Valley have demanded the provincial and federal
government to send doctors' teams and medicines to the affected areas
to stop the further spread of the epidemic.

--
